               <msContents>
                  <summary>Images 2r-186r: Psalter. Iluminations added recently over text. The midpoint of the Psalms may be marked with a slight indentation of the line (image 76l, line 9). Psalm 151 is the short version. The Song of Songs has the common edition in the base hand with additions in the margins from the Old Giyorgis recension. Praises of Mary, written with musical notation through Thursday, begins with Monday and culminates on Sunday. Image 186r contains a note of ownership with a secondary owner, and a curse for stealing or effacing the book. Images 187l-187r: List of feast days of the apostles and saints. Images 188r: Asmat prayers. Illuminations are added recently over text.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <textLang/>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
